article_title: Gov. Butch Otter’s Idaho health care plan in jeopardy; what happened and what’s next?
article_text:
Committee votes not to hear bill to fund Otter health plan

It’s technically alive, but no further action without money questions resolved

Lead House sponsor: ‘I suspect PCAP is dead’

article_metadata.news-keywords: Idaho, legislature, Medicaid expansion, PCAP, Primary Care Access Program, Dr., Fred Wood, ID, Iowa, insurance, Otter, Ottercare
article_metadata.description: The Idaho primary care plan has failed its first test of broader legislative support in the House on questions over funding. Here’s a Q&A on where things stand.
